If you want to make a change you have to start where you stand. The Cultural Enrichment Center offers a space for black youth in Fort Collins, CO to explore their identity and find their voice. If, like us, you believe in the work @cec_foco is doing, become a monthly donor at www.fococec.org/donate.

Kindling was brewed to give back 1% of revenue to our nonprofit partners, like @cec_foco, who create positive impact and lasting change.

Last year, the Cameron Peak fire destroyed over 208,000 acres. Wildlands Restoration Volunteers and their network of amazing volunteers have been working tirelessly to mitigate the damage and restore the land. ⁠
⁠
We couldn't be more grateful to be their partner and love to get our hands dirty with them on volunteer days. By volunteering with @wrv.restore, you’ll meet great people, heal the land and build community. Sign up for a volunteer project today by clicking the link in bio. ⁠

node.text:
The 2021 Hop Harvest has officially begun! Last week, our brewers traveled to Oregon to check out what this year's hop harvest has in store and hand-select the best Strata @indiehops for a wet hop brew. These hops left the vine, traveled to the brewery, and made it in the boil in under 24 hours. We can't wait for you to try this one. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Look for the Fresh Strata Hop IPA @odellbrewingsloans, @odellbrewingfivepoints, and at the Fort Collins Taproom in 4 pack 16oz cans in a couple of weeks! Stay tuned.

Hey Fort Collins! Join us on Sunday, August 22nd as we celebrate active living and the stewardship of the outdoors for Colorado Wellness Day. We'll have @allkindkombucha tastings, local outdoor vendors, food trucks, and live music from Rusty 44 at our Fort Collins Taproom.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
See you there!⁠

node.text:
Double Pilsner is back for a special small batch, taproom release! This limited 4-pack is available at all three taprooms on Friday, August 20th. Head to the Fort Collins Taproom, @odellbrewingsloans, or @odellbrewingfivepoints to grab your 4pack - they'll likely go fast!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Refreshing and delicate yet bold and assertive, the Double Pilsner's golden straw color leaves nowhere for imperfections to hide. Scents of pilsner malt and light floral hop aromas combine with a rich malt flavor to create a balanced and warming Imperial Pilsner.⁠
